---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Flowers — Bloom Your Way to Victory"
  description="Flower words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. ORCHID (12pts), ZINNIA (15pts), DAHLIA (10pts). Botanical flower names for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble flower words, orchid scrabble points, zinnia scrabble, dahlia scrabble word, flower names scrabble, botanical words scrabble, garden flowers scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Flowers — Bloom Your Way to Victory","description":"Flower words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. ORCHID (12pts), ZINNIA (15pts), DAHLIA (10pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening-flowers"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is ZINNIA a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! ZINNIA scores 15 points (Z=10, I=1, N=1, N=1, I=1, A=1). The Z tile alone provides 10 of the 15 points. It's a colourful garden flower and valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is ORCHID worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ORCHID scores 12 points (O=1, R=1, C=3, H=4, I=1, D=2). The C+H combination contributes 7 points. It's a popular exotic flower valid in all Scrabble dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play DAHLIA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! DAHLIA scores 10 points (D=2, A=1, H=4, L=1, I=1, A=1). Named after botanist Anders Dahl, it's a valid 6-letter play with H=4 as the primary scorer."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Flowers — Bloom Your Way to Victory</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Flower names bring unexpected scoring power to the Scrabble board. ZINNIA deploys the Z tile for 15 points, while ORCHID combines C and H for 12 points from common letters. These botanical beauties are easy to remember and surprisingly effective in competitive play.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZINNIA (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ORCHID</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DAHLIA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PEONY</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Flower Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">�� Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ZINNIA — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Z=10, I=1, N=1, N=1, I=1, A=1 · 6 letters · Uses Z tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A bright daisy-family flower named after Johann Zinn. ZINNIA scores 15 points with Z=10 doing most of the work. The remaining letters (I, N, N, I, A) are among the most common tiles in the bag — making this word very drawable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌺 ORCHID</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · O=1, R=1, C=3, H=4, I=1, D=2 · Exotic flower</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌸 DAHLIA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · D=2, A=1, H=4, L=1, I=1, A=1 · Garden bloom</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌷 PEONY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · P=3, E=1, O=1, N=1, Y=4 · Fragrant bloom</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌻 ASTER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · A=1, S=1, T=1, E=1, R=1 · Star-shaped flower</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Playable Flower Names</h2>
      <p>These flower names are all valid in competitive Scrabble:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PANSY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POPPY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TULIP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LILAC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">IRIS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CROCUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Flower Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZINNIA deploys Z with common tiles:</span> Unlike QUIZ or QUARTZ which need specific letters, ZINNIA only needs Z plus I, N, N, I, A — all high-frequency draws. When you get Z, think ZINNIA first.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ORCHID uses the CH cluster:</span> C=3 and H=4 together yield 7 points from two tiles. ORCHID wraps them in four common letters (O, R, I, D) for a reliable 12-point play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">POPPY for double-P racks:</span> Drawing two P tiles? POPPY (14pts) uses both P=3 tiles plus Y=4, turning an awkward combination into a solid score with duplicate letters.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Flower words are <span class="text-white font-medium">memorability champions</span>. Unlike obscure Scrabble words, everyone knows ZINNIA, ORCHID, and DAHLIA — making them easy to recall under time pressure. They use Z, CH, and Y combinations efficiently and are worth committing to your active vocabulary.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gardening</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/nature-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Nature Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid flower word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
